==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Contraries
<hw>Con"tra*ries</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ <?/; 48)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[Pl. of <er>Contrary</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Logic)</fld>
<def>Propositions which directly and destructively contradict each
other, but of which the falsehood of one does not establish the truth of
the other.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If two universals differ in quality, they are
<qex>contraries</qex>; as, every vine is a tree; no vine is a tree.
These can never be both true together; but they may be both false.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contrariety</ent>⟦br⟧
